---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import PolicyArticle from "../components/layout/PolicyArticle.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
---

<MainLayout title="Terms of Service">
  <PolicyArticle title="Crystord: Terms of Service" updatedAt="June 8, 2026">

    <section>
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of all Crystord products and services
      operated by Aleutheris ("we", "us", "our"), a company registered in the Netherlands. By
      installing, accessing, or using any Crystord product you agree to be bound by these Terms. If
      you do not agree, do not install or use our products.</p>

      <p>These Terms cover both:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The <strong>Crystord Google Workspace Add-on</strong> (the "Add-on"), available from the
        Google Workspace Marketplace, which synchronises data from Google Sheets™ into Google
        Slides™ presentations.</li>
        <li>The <strong>Crystord web application</strong> at
        <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a> (the "App"), which provides
        account management and authentication for the Crystord platform.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Description of the Service</h2>

      <h3>Google Workspace Add-on</h3>
      <p>The Add-on enables Google Workspace users to define placeholder variables in a Google
      Slides™ presentation and bind them to data in a connected Google Sheets™ spreadsheet. When
      synchronisation is run, the Add-on reads the specified sheet data and replaces placeholder
      content in the presentation. The Add-on supports text and numeric values and is limited to
      integration between Google Sheets™ and Slides™. Service depends on availability of Google
      Workspace APIs.</p>

      <h3>Crystord Web Application</h3>
      <p>The App provides an authenticated web interface for managing your Crystord account. It
      allows you to sign in to access platform features and account settings. The App requires a
      valid Crystord account and functions as a companion to the Add-on.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Account Registration and Use</h2>
      <p>To use the App you must create a Crystord account with a valid email address. You are
      responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your credentials and for all activity
      that occurs under your account. Notify us immediately of any unauthorised use at
      <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</p>
      <p>You must be at least 16 years old to create a Crystord account. Use of the Add-on without
      an account is governed by your Google Workspace administrator's installation policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree to use Crystord products only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these
      Terms. You must not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use either product to process data in violation of applicable laws or third-party
        rights.</li>
        <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or circumvent security or authentication mechanisms in
        the App or Add-on.</li>
        <li>Test or probe for vulnerabilities in the App without our written permission.</li>
        <li>Use automated tools to access the App at a rate or volume that impairs service
        availability.</li>
        <li>Misrepresent your identity or affiliation when registering an account.</li>
        <li>License, sell, resell, or otherwise exploit either product except as permitted by
        these Terms.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Google Workspace Permissions</h2>
      <p>The Add-on requests access to Google Sheets™ and Slides™ in your Google account. By
      granting these permissions, you authorise the Add-on to read sheet data from sources you
      connect and to write updated content to the presentations you are editing. You may revoke
      these permissions at any time via
      <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.</p>
      <p>Aleutheris' use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
      <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
      including the Limited Use Requirements.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>User Content and Data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Add-on:</strong> Google Sheets™ and Slides™ content is processed transiently
        within your Google environment and is never stored on Aleutheris servers. All data resides
        within your Google account.</li>
        <li><strong>App:</strong> Your email address and authentication credentials are stored
        securely to maintain your account. See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for full
        detail on what is collected, how it is used, and your rights.</li>
        <li>You retain full ownership of your Google documents and account data.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Retention and User Rights</h2>
      <h3>Add-on</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No external storage:</strong> No Google document content is stored on
        Aleutheris servers. Processing is session-based and transient.</li>
        <li><strong>Access revocation:</strong> You may revoke Add-on permissions at any time via
        Google Account security settings, which immediately stops all data access.</li>
        <li><strong>Uninstall:</strong> Uninstalling the Add-on removes all associated Google
        account permissions and ends all data access.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Web Application</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account deletion:</strong> You may request deletion of your account and all
        associated data at any time by contacting
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>. Requests are
        processed within 30 days.</li>
        <li><strong>Data access:</strong> You may contact us to request a summary of what personal
        data is held on your account.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

